            <article class="article-content">
                <p>In July 1947, on a hot summer day, a rancher found pieces of debris all over his remote New Mexico property. The US military would say they found a "flying disc" within hours, but the next day they would say it was just a weather balloon. This chain of events set off what would become the most famous UFO sighting in history. It turned a small military town into the center of alien speculation and government conspiracy theories that still exist almost 80 years later.</p>

